Duplicate tensile stress–strain curves for Ti–6Al–4Nb and Ti–6Al–4Fe alloys are presented in Fig. 9
. Yielding was not observed for Ti–6Al–4Fe alloy. This alloy exhibited brittle fracture and yield stress was equated to ultimate tensile stress. Variation was observed in duplicated experiments for Ti–6Al–4Fe alloy (Table 2
). The duplicated values for ultimate tensile stress and yield stress from the two experiments were similar in case of Ti–6Al–4Nb alloy (Table 2).
